Cell[TextData[{
 "\tProbably the most important instance of the Poisson distribution is in \
the study of what is called the ",
 StyleBox["Poisson process",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". A Poisson process records the cumulative number of occurrences of some \
phenomenon as time increases. Therefore, such a process is not just a single \
random variable, but a family of random variables (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "t"], TraditionalForm]]],
 ") indexed by a variable ",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " usually thought of as time.  We interpret ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "t"], TraditionalForm]]],
 " as the number of occurrences of the phenomenon in [0, ",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "].  ",
 StyleBox["A family of random variables such as this is called generically a ",
  FontColor->GrayLevel[0]],
 StyleBox["stochastic process",
  FontSlant->"Italic",
  FontColor->GrayLevel[0]],
 StyleBox[".  We will cover stochastic processes in more detail, and also say \
more about the Poisson process, in Chapter 6.",
  FontColor->GrayLevel[0]],
 "\n\tSince occurrences happen singly and randomly, and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "t"], TraditionalForm]]],
 " counts the total number of them, if for a fixed experimental outcome \
\[Omega] we plot ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["X", "t"], TraditionalForm]]],
 "(\[Omega]) as a function of ",
 StyleBox["t",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " we get a non-decreasing step function starting at 0, which jumps by \
exactly 1 at the random times ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "1"], TraditionalForm]]],
 "(\[Omega]), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "2"], TraditionalForm]]],
 "(\[Omega]), ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "3"], TraditionalForm]]],
 "(\[Omega]), ... of occurrence of the phenomenon. Such a function, called a ",
 StyleBox["sample path",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of the process, is shown in Figure 13, for the case where the first three \
jumps occur at times ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["T", "1"], "=", "1.2"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["T", "2"], "=", "2.0"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["T", "3"], "=", "3.4"}]}], TraditionalForm]]],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.425080223261142*^9, 3.425080297356142*^9}, {
   3.4250803403591423`*^9, 3.425080341213142*^9}, 3.456587112719183*^9}],

